  <h1 class="topictitle1">Topic Editing Tips</h1>
 
   
  <div><p>Tips for editing topic content.
  </p>

	 <p>The 
		<span class="wintitle">Element List</span> container is almost like the 
		<span class="wintitle">Styles and Formatting</span> task pane in 
		<span class="wintitle">MS Word</span>. To apply an element in a topic, you can
		either:
	 </p>

	 <br /><a name="concept_F19561AED74E4F61A1D5F7E602C4E1FF__ul_2B5F166038204CF08A158844AE0CF8B9"><!-- --></a><ul id="concept_F19561AED74E4F61A1D5F7E602C4E1FF__ul_2B5F166038204CF08A158844AE0CF8B9">
		<li id="concept_F19561AED74E4F61A1D5F7E602C4E1FF__li_CCC1602A3E4F4DA883C46F2ED5253B8C"><a name="concept_F19561AED74E4F61A1D5F7E602C4E1FF__li_CCC1602A3E4F4DA883C46F2ED5253B8C"><!-- --></a>select the text and then
		  double-click the element you want to apply, or
		</li>

		<li id="concept_F19561AED74E4F61A1D5F7E602C4E1FF__li_D677B703798C419E9AEB175739205908"><a name="concept_F19561AED74E4F61A1D5F7E602C4E1FF__li_D677B703798C419E9AEB175739205908"><!-- --></a>double-click the element
		  name which will insert the element wherever the cursor is in the 
		  <span class="wintitle">View</span> container, then type the text.
		</li>

	 </ul>

	 <div class="section" id="concept_F19561AED74E4F61A1D5F7E602C4E1FF__section_310FBF221B9F4B4EA846C4D7AB17221A"><a name="concept_F19561AED74E4F61A1D5F7E602C4E1FF__section_310FBF221B9F4B4EA846C4D7AB17221A"><!-- --></a><h2 class="sectiontitle">Formatting</h2>
		
		<p>Use the 
		  <var class="varname">wintitle</var> element for program names, container names,
		  and dialog box window names. Examples: 
		  <span class="wintitle">Windows Explorer</span>, 
		  <span class="wintitle">XMetaL</span>, 
		  <span class="wintitle">VELOX</span>, 
		  <span class="wintitle">Recent configurations</span> container, 
		  <span class="wintitle">Qualification logic</span> container, 
		  <span class="wintitle">Edit Deliverable Type</span> window, 
		  <span class="wintitle">TortoiseSVN Commit</span> progress window, etc.
		</p>

		<p>Use the 
		  <var class="varname">uicontrol</var> element for items on the screen the reader
		  will interact with, e.g. click the 
		  <span class="uicontrol">Close</span> button. If multiple interactions are
		  required, apply the 
		  <var class="varname">uicontrol</var> element for each stage of the interaction,
		  then select all the stages and apply the 
		  <var class="varname">menucascade</var> element. When 
		  <span class="wintitle">XMetaL</span> applies the 
		  <var class="varname">menucascade</var> element, it replaces any spaces between
		  the 
		  <var class="varname">uicontrol</var> elements with a " &gt; ", e.g., select 
		  <span class="menucascade"><span class="uicontrol">File</span> 
			  &gt; <span class="uicontrol">Open</span> 
			  &gt; <span class="uicontrol">Template</span></span> to open an existing
		  template.
		</p>

		<p>Use the 
		  <var class="varname">filepath</var> element for file names and folder paths, ,
		  e.g., 
		  <span class="filepath">filename.doc</span> is at 
		  <span class="filepath">c:\username\My Documents</span>.
		</p>

	 </div>

  </div>

